A pair calling presumably triggered by the Crested Goshawk that flew through its terrotory with a dead Water Monitor Lizard. The Crested Goshawk in the background is the same individual as that in Goshawk, Crested_2020-04-02_1038_SG_WCP. The first indivudal that calls is a presumed male and the response is from a presumed female (sexed based on plumage intensity). The male is the same individual as the recording by me from the same site, same day, recorded at 1043.

A pair of Collared Kingfishers held territory (I observed them copulating about 15 minutes ago) and another Collared Kingfisher (sex unsure) intruded the territory of this pair. First section few seconds of the sound recording is from that interaction. The female of the pair chased the intruder away and they both flew off. The second section of the call was from the direction that both birds flew off to, but I am uncertain whether it was the intruder or defender that called. This is a different pair from all other recordings of this species uploaded by me from the same site as of 9 July 2020.
Presumed male based on deep blue upperparts colouration
